## 4. Core Analytical Modules
The application is logically partitioned into specialized analytical hubs.

### 4.1 Tournament Overview
This module gives a macroscopic view of the historical landscape.
* **Dynamic Insights Ticker:** A scrolling marquee displaying high-level KPIs like total sixes, wickets fallen, and highest scores.
* **Venue Fortresses:** A unique mapping of "Team + Venue" dominance. It utilizes interactive scatter and horizontal bar charts to identify elite fortresses—stadiums where specific teams hold significant historical win percentages.
* **City Match Density:** A custom lollipop chart visualizing the geographical spread of matches across the top 25 host cities globally.

### 4.2 Team & Toss Analysis
Focuses on the psychological and tactical profile of international squads.
* **Toss Advantage Reality Check:** Donut charts that analyze the correlation between winning the toss and winning the match, supplemented by area charts tracking captains' decisions (Bat vs. Field) over time.
* **Team DNA (Tornado Chart):** A symmetric profile demonstrating whether a specific team operates better by *Setting Targets* (Defending) or *Chasing*. This completely shifts the narrative from "how many games they won" to "how they play to win."

### 4.3 Advanced Head-to-Head Player Scouting
The most granular hub in the project, designed for deep head-to-head comparisons between any two batters or bowlers, discarding irrelevant noise (like comparing against wides).

**Batter Deep Dive:**
* **Efficiency & Survival Rates:** Metrics such as Balls Per Dismissal (BPD) to quantify crease survival, alongside Boundary Dependency and Dot Ball Percentages.
* **Phase Specialization:** Radar and bar charts comparing Strike Rates across the Powerplay, Middle, and Death overs.
* **Match-up Analytics:** Direct statistical splits regarding performance against Pace versus Spin.
* **Partnership Dependency:** Investigating how a batter's strike rate fluctuates depending on whether their non-striker is an "Aggressor" (career SR ≥ 140) or an "Anchor."

**Bowler Deep Dive:**
* **Pressure & Leakage:** Measuring Scoreboard Pressure via Dot Ball percentages, specifically in high-tension scenarios like the Death Overs.
* **Wicket Quality Assessment:** Categorizing wickets to determine whether a bowler relies on pure skill (Bowled/LBW) or capitalizing on mistakes (Caught).
* **Phase Survival DNA:** Economy rate profiling via radar charts to identify exactly when a captain should deploy a specific bowler.

### 4.4 In-Depth Match Analytics & Ultimate Team Clash
An exploration of match trends and head-to-head franchise metrics.
* **Extras Breakdown:** Normalizing the average number of wides, no-balls, and byes conceded per match by different teams.
* **Evolution of Intent:** Spline-curve line charts tracking the historical shift in Run Rates across different match phases.
* **Ultimate Team Clash:** An isolation tool that recalculates every analytical metric (from Batting Efficiency to Bowling Discipline) solely for deliveries bowled *between* two specific selected teams.

### 4.5 Modern Meta Analytics (2023-2025 Focus)
Cricket has fundamentally changed in the last three years. This module captures the modern aggressive meta.
* **Run Inflation:** Visualized via a smoothed area chart, highlighting the spike in average 1st innings scores triggered by modern aggression and rule changes.
* **The Intent Matrix (Gear Shifting):** A scatter plot matrix that maps a player's "Initial Strike Rate" (balls 1-10) against their "Settled Strike Rate" (balls 11+). This categorizes players into Elite Aggressors vs. Classic Anchors and generates an "Acceleration Curve" for individual batters.

